      限定符和类型 类和说明
      interface  Beta
      Signifies that a public API (public class, method or field) is subject to incompatible changes, or even removal, in a future release.
      interface  UBTInCompatible
      The presence of this annotation on a method indicates that the method may not be used with the UtilsBaseToolkit(UBT), even though its type is annotated as UBTCompatible and accessible in UBT.
      interface  VisibleForTesting
      Annotates a program element that exists, or is more widely visible than otherwise necessary, only for use in test code.
